### Example that showed the overhanging base:
###		/home/isovic/work/eclipse-workspace/graphmap/bin/graphmap-not_release -x illumina -v 7 -t 1 -n 1 -y 0 -r data/offending_ref.fasta -d data/offending_seq.fa -o data/out8_xillumina.sam 2>&1 | tee out8_xillumina.tee
### The issue was fixed in commit 41ae30b0d8603469c62794cba1960dc42f739d4e. There was a bug with localization of the approximate alignment position (using Myers) before SeqAn's Gotoh was applied. Concretely:
### Commit comment: Fixed the bug reported by Andreas (Issue #14: Alignment out of reference bounds). The problem was in localization of the region for alignment (SeqAnSemiglobalWrapperWithMyersLocalization). When this condition is satisfied: 'if (localized_end >= reference_length)', the localized_end = reference_length - 1. This was a problem because inf_target was initialized using (localized_end - localized_start + 1), and thus would be out of bounds. Also, in this commit, SeqAn 1.4.2 was replaced by SeqAn 2.0.1.

